af017424-3cef-420a-a391-f20dfe0424f5	\N	2026-06-15 11:57:45.948068	citrus fruits	Blue Mold	harvested fruits	85%	fungal	fast	Medium	["blue-green fuzzy mold on fruit surface", "fruit decay and softening", "discoloration of peel"]	The image shows citrus fruits with blue-green mold patches, typical of Penicillium mold (Blue Mold) which affects harvested citrus fruits during storage or transportation.	diseased	Blue Mold — fungal pathogen affecting citrus fruits	The citrus fruits show blue-green fuzzy mold patches typical of Blue Mold (Penicillium species), along with fruit decay, softening, and discoloration of the peel. These symptoms usually appear during storage or transportation.	["Remove and discard all infected fruits to reduce the spread of the mold.", "Use Pyraclostrobin (Kairun) fungicide by mixing 10 grams with 30 jin of water and spray evenly on the fruits and storage areas.", "Ensure good ventilation and reduce humidity in storage to slow fungal growth.", "Repeat the fungicide application every 7 days for 2-3 applications to control the disease effectively.", "Clean and disinfect storage containers and transport vehicles before use."]	["Handle fruits carefully to avoid wounds that can be entry points for the mold.", "Store citrus fruits in cool, dry, and well-ventilated conditions to inhibit fungal growth.", "Regularly inspect stored fruits and remove any showing early signs of mold."]	[{"product_id": "PN0002", "name": "Pyraclostrobin (Kairun)", "product_type": "pesticide", "ingredients": "Active ingredient: Pyraclostrobin 250 g/L", "spec": "100 grams", "how_to_use": "Mix 10 grams of Pyraclostrobin with 30 jin of water and spray evenly on the citrus fruits and storage environment to control Blue Mold.", "frequency": "Apply every 7 days for 2-3 applications", "caution": "Avoid overuse to prevent resistance development; follow recommended dosage and intervals.", "match_score": 0.5744, "source": "rag"}, {"product_id": "PN0034", "name": "1.8% Xingjunamine Acetate", "product_type": "pesticide", "ingredients": "Active ingredient: Oxyphenidyl 1.26%", "spec": "200g/500g/1000g", "how_to_use": "Crop/Location Control Target Dosage (Preparation Dose/Acre) Application Method Apple rust: 160-320 times dilution (spray) Apple rot: 200-300 times dilution (apply to wounds) Technical Requirements: 1", "frequency": "Every 7-10 days", "caution": "Follow label instructions", "match_score": 0.3199, "source": "rag"}, {"product_id": "PN0029", "name": "6% Kasugamycin", "product_type": "pesticide", "ingredients": "Active ingredient: Kasugamycin 6%", "spec": "500 grams", "how_to_use": "Target pests: Rice blast", "frequency": "Every 7-10 days", "caution": "Follow label instructions", "match_score": 0.2416, "source": "rag"}]
1971ce1a-b81d-435b-9545-6ffeb37dfc9c	1830b0b7-3035-49d6-9200-6ee32b9b2bf9	2026-06-19 10:57:46.782458	tomato	blossom end rot	fruiting	90%	nutrient deficiency	moderate	Medium	["sunken black necrotic area on fruit end", "discoloration and softening of fruit tissue", "cracking and lesions near affected area"]	The image shows a ripe tomato fruit with a dark, sunken patch and surrounding tissue decay typical of blossom end rot caused by calcium deficiency. The presence of ripe fruit and the typical shape and color confirm the crop and growth stage.	diseased	blossom end rot — nutrient deficiency	The tomato fruit shows a dark, sunken black necrotic area on the fruit end, discoloration and softening of the fruit tissue, and cracking and lesions near the affected area. These symptoms are typical of blossom end rot caused by calcium deficiency.	["Ensure consistent watering to avoid fluctuations in soil moisture, which can worsen calcium uptake problems.", "Apply calcium-containing foliar sprays or soil amendments to increase calcium availability to the plants.", "Avoid excessive nitrogen fertilization which can inhibit calcium uptake.", "Mulch around the plants to maintain soil moisture and temperature.", "Remove affected fruits to reduce secondary infections and improve plant health."]	["Maintain even soil moisture by regular watering and mulching to prevent calcium deficiency.", "Avoid excessive nitrogen fertilizer application, which can reduce calcium uptake.", "Use soil tests to monitor and adjust calcium levels before planting."]	[{"product_id": "PN0002", "name": "Pyraclostrobin (Kairun)", "product_type": "pesticide", "ingredients": "Active ingredient: Pyraclostrobin 250 g/L", "spec": "100 grams", "how_to_use": "Although Pyraclostrobin is a pesticide and not directly effective against nutrient deficiency, if fungal diseases are suspected alongside, mix 10 grams with 30 jin of water and spray evenly on the tomato plants.", "frequency": "Use as needed based on disease presence, following label instructions.", "caution": "Do not overuse to prevent resistance development.", "match_score": 0.5134, "source": "rag"}, {"product_id": "PN0029", "name": "6% Kasugamycin", "product_type": "pesticide", "ingredients": "Active ingredient: Kasugamycin 6%", "spec": "500 grams", "how_to_use": "Kasugamycin is not effective for blossom end rot or nutrient deficiencies; it is for rice blast and tobacco wildfire control and should not be used on tomatoes.", "frequency": "Not applicable for tomato blossom end rot.", "caution": "Use only on recommended crops and diseases to avoid crop damage.", "match_score": 0.4842, "source": "rag"}, {"product_id": "PN0007", "name": "3% Metalaxyl-Hymexazol", "product_type": "pesticide", "ingredients": "Active ingredients: Hymexazol 2.5%, Metalaxyl 0.5%; Total active ingredients: Metalaxyl-M 3% (Active ingredients and their contents: Hymexazol 2.5%, Metalaxyl 0.5%)", "spec": "1000g/500g/100g", "how_to_use": "This product targets damping-off disease in rice seedlings and is not suitable for treating blossom end rot in tomatoes.", "frequency": "Not applicable for tomato blossom end rot.", "caution": "Use only on recommended crops and diseases to avoid ineffective treatment.", "match_score": 0.4256, "source": "rag"}]
702d17c5-8c1e-43b4-8772-8537f67dba76	1830b0b7-3035-49d6-9200-6ee32b9b2bf9	2026-06-19 10:59:36.3297	citrus fruits (lemons and oranges)	blue mold (Penicillium mold)	post-harvest	90%	fungal	fast	Medium	["blue-green fuzzy mold spots", "white powdery mold growth", "fruit decay and discoloration"]	The fruits show blue and white powdery mold spots, which are indicative of blue mold caused by Penicillium species. The fruits are mature and harvested, as they are separated from the plant.	diseased	blue mold (Penicillium mold) — fungal pathogen	The citrus fruits show visible blue-green fuzzy mold spots and white powdery mold growth, which are typical symptoms of blue mold caused by Penicillium species. The fruits are mature and harvested, exhibiting fruit decay and discoloration.	["Remove and discard all affected fruits to reduce the spread of the mold.", "Ensure proper storage conditions with good ventilation and low humidity to slow mold growth.", "Apply fungicides as per the instructions below to control the fungal infection.", "Avoid handling fruits when wet to prevent spreading spores.", "Monitor fruits regularly for any new signs of mold and repeat treatments if necessary."]	["Store harvested fruits in cool, dry, and well-ventilated areas to inhibit mold growth.", "Handle fruits carefully to avoid bruising, which can increase susceptibility to blue mold.", "Regularly inspect stored fruits and promptly remove any showing signs of mold to prevent spread."]	[{"product_id": "PN0002", "name": "Pyraclostrobin (Kairun)", "product_type": "pesticide", "ingredients": "Active ingredient: Pyraclostrobin 250 g/L", "spec": "100 grams", "how_to_use": "Mix 10 grams of Pyraclostrobin (Kairun) with 30 jin of water and spray on the harvested citrus fruits showing blue mold symptoms to control fungal growth.", "frequency": "Apply once and repeat every 7-10 days if symptoms persist, up to 3 applications.", "caution": "Avoid overuse to prevent resistance development; follow recommended doses.", "match_score": 0.3316, "source": "rag"}, {"product_id": "PN0034", "name": "1.8% Xingjunamine Acetate", "product_type": "pesticide", "ingredients": "Active ingredient: Oxyphenidyl 1.26%", "spec": "200g/500g/1000g", "how_to_use": "Dilute 50 grams of 1.8% Xingjunamine Acetate with 30 jin of water and apply by spraying on harvested fruits with visible blue mold spots and decay.", "frequency": "Apply 2-3 times consecutively with 7-10 days interval between applications.", "caution": "Do not apply during midday heat; spray before 10:00 AM or after 1:00 PM.", "match_score": 0.3213, "source": "rag"}, {"product_id": "PN0029", "name": "6% Kasugamycin", "product_type": "pesticide", "ingredients": "Active ingredient: Kasugamycin 6%", "spec": "500 grams", "how_to_use": "Dilute 45 grams of 6% Kasugamycin with 30 jin of water and spray evenly on harvested citrus fruits affected by blue mold to reduce fungal infection.", "frequency": "Apply once every 7-10 days for 2-3 consecutive applications.", "caution": "Reapply if rain occurs within 3 hours of spraying to maintain effectiveness.", "match_score": 0.2458, "source": "rag"}]
89ccb141-bbf6-4055-9a1e-0419d205bc10	1830b0b7-3035-49d6-9200-6ee32b9b2bf9	2026-06-19 11:07:35.599715	citrus fruits	Blue Mold	post-harvest	90%	fungal	fast	moderate	["blue-green mold patches", "softening of fruit skin", "discoloration", "fruit decay"]	The affected fruits show typical signs of Blue Mold caused by Penicillium species, characterized by blue-green fuzzy mold growth on the rind post-harvest.	diseased	Blue Mold — fungal pathogen (Penicillium species)	The citrus fruits show moderate infection with Blue Mold, characterized by blue-green mold patches on the rind, softening of the fruit skin, discoloration, and fruit decay. These symptoms typically appear post-harvest and indicate fungal growth that can rapidly spoil the fruit.	["Remove and discard all infected fruits to prevent spread of the mold.", "Ensure good air circulation and reduce humidity in storage areas to slow fungal growth.", "Apply fungicides promptly according to the recommended dilution and usage instructions.", "Handle fruits carefully to avoid wounds that can serve as infection sites.", "Monitor treated fruits regularly and repeat applications as advised."]	["Store citrus fruits in well-ventilated, dry conditions to reduce humidity and fungal growth.", "Handle fruits gently during harvest and post-harvest to avoid skin damage.", "Regularly inspect stored fruits and promptly remove any showing signs of mold or decay."]	[{"product_id": "PN0002", "name": "Pyraclostrobin (Kairun)", "product_type": "pesticide", "ingredients": "Active ingredient: Pyraclostrobin 250 g/L", "spec": "100 grams", "how_to_use": "Mix 10 grams of Pyraclostrobin with 30 jin of water and spray evenly on citrus fruits and storage areas to control Blue Mold.", "frequency": "Apply as needed, observing fruit condition; repeat applications can be done following label recommendations.", "caution": "Avoid overuse to prevent resistance development; follow label dosage strictly.", "match_score": 0.5744, "source": "rag"}, {"product_id": "PN0034", "name": "1.8% Xingjunamine Acetate", "product_type": "pesticide", "ingredients": "Active ingredient: Oxyphenidyl 1.26%", "spec": "200g/500g/1000g", "how_to_use": "Dilute 50 grams of product with 30 jin of water and spray on citrus fruits, especially targeting wounds and infected areas to control fungal growth.", "frequency": "Apply 2-3 times consecutively with 7-10 days interval between applications.", "caution": "Do not apply during midday heat; apply before 10:00 AM or after 1:00 PM for best efficacy.", "match_score": 0.3199, "source": "rag"}, {"product_id": "PN0029", "name": "6% Kasugamycin", "product_type": "pesticide", "ingredients": "Active ingredient: Kasugamycin 6%", "spec": "500 grams", "how_to_use": "Although primarily for rice and tobacco diseases, dilute 45 grams with 30 jin of water and spray evenly on citrus fruits as a supplementary treatment against fungal pathogens.", "frequency": "Apply once every 7-10 days, for 2-3 consecutive applications.", "caution": "Avoid application before rain or windy conditions; reapply if rain occurs within 3 hours.", "match_score": 0.2416, "source": "rag"}]
